As we wrap up our theme of Food & Migration, Origins, and Seeds, I am sharing 5️⃣ fundamental things you need to know about seeds:

1. Seeds are the very essence of life, one of the main (hidden) pillars of our civilization, eons of ecosystem's evolution and memory encoded in DNA.

2. The richness of global "heritage" owes more to intercontinental seed and cultural exchange (and travel technologies) than to any other factors. Global food culture benefits from exchange and diversity.

3. We are losing seed diversity at an alarming rate -wiping out thousands of years of agricultural curation and culture-  and we must act.

4. Seed-saving preserves our food culture, and the best form of seed saving is by planting them! 

5. Biodiversity of seeds is essential in our efforts for a regenerative world, for a resilient, abundant and fair food system, and to accomplish the SDGs.

Please add to the list of what you think we should all know about seeds in the comments! ⬇️

Stay tuned! Our next big theme will be on #PleasureActivism ✊🏽🤤

“The Earth is the only world known so far to harbor life. There is nowhere else, at least in the near future, to which our species could migrate. Visit, yes. Settle, not yet. Like it or not, for the moment the Earth is where we make our stand.

There is perhaps no better demonstration of the folly of human conceits than this distant image of our tiny world. To me, it underscores our responsibility to deal more kindly with one another, and to preserve and cherish the pale blue dot, the only home we've ever known.” 
- Carl Sagan, Pale Blue Dot

node.text:
Combining pleasure and meaning was all we set out to do with Rodrigo on #TheFinalTable. Every single one of our dishes/creations was intended to delight the senses, through artistry and craft. But not only: each dish also had a clear purpose to provoke and express the importance of food as medium. 

We showcased insects as food as a solution to the negative environmental impact of protein-rich diets, raised awareness about the urgency of addressing deforestation in the Amazon, elevated historical truths about beloved rituals such as Thanksgiving... many of you got here after watching the show, and I am so grateful for it.

This Sunday, September 19th at 1500 UTC, in my #LiveCookingClass with @charlesxmichelpatrons, I will share the ideas and concept I planned to cook for the finale. Alongside walking you through my drafts and sketches, I will also prepare #live some of the most precious, subtle expressions of my cooking.

Want to learn more - click the link in my stories or bio! 🔗

I believe our existence in the 21st century is inherently political—more than ever—especially in the way we live and eat. It is my hope that a regenerative approach can actually inspire more of us to embody our craft, whatever it may be, with more purpose as we add our grain of sand in the face of current challenges 🌊

node.text:
This Thursday, I will host a very special IG Live on 🥄 Eating Utensils & Pleasure 🥄with my dear friend @AndreasFabianDesign (German Designer, Silversmith, and PhD in Spoons) co-founder of @_MichelFabian_ 

Michel/Fabian (M/F) designs culinary utensils and vessels to optimize sensory experience, enhancing pleasure and encouraging conscious consumption.

During the #iglive, Andreas and I will share about the M/F Goûte Spoon (inspired by the universal act of licking fingers in an elegant manner), research in the field of gastrophysics, and how culinary technology can be designed to increase eating pleasure. 👆🏽👅

See you there! 📅 Thursday, September 9th, 15:00 UTC

#MichelFabianDesign #GoûteSpoon #gastrophysics #fooddesign #consciouseating #pleasure #scienceandart #eatingutensils

The #FoodPainting in this photo from my last #LiveCookingClass with @charlesxmichelpatrons was an effort to combine purpose and pleasure.

I truly believe our activism doesn’t have to be a painstaking climb, rather it can (and should?) be a growthful journey of joy and prosperity. 

This Saturday September 4th at 15:00 UTC , we’ll continue the conversation on "Food & Pleasure," this time specifically around pleasure in activism. 

In what ways do you combine purpose and pleasure? Let me know in the comments below. ⬇️ And please feel free to ask me a question  or share your thoughts on this topic… I may reflect on it on Saturday! 

#foodandpleasure #pleasureactivism #consciouseating #moderation #foodeducation #foodactivism #adriannemareebrown #inspo #liveqanda
______

El “Food Painting” (pintura con alimentos) en esta foto de mi última #ClasedeCocinaenVivo con @charlesxmichelpatrons fue un esfuerzo para combinar propósito y placer. Estoy convencido que el activismo no tiene que ser una batalla de sacrificios, sino que puede (y debe?) ser un camino de crecimiento, alegría y prosperidad.

Este sábado 4 de septiembre a las 15:00 UTC, continuaremos la conversación sobre "Comida y placer", esta vez específicamente en torno al placer en el activismo.

On this video, … my answer to the question: “What is your guilty pleasure?” in a Live Q&A with my @charlesxmichelpatrons back in June 2019.

“Sola dosis facit venenum” /// “The dose makes the poison” 🌿💊 a condensed version of chemist and philosopher Paracelsus’ maxim, “All things are poison, and nothing is without poison; the dosage alone makes it so a thing is not a poison.”

Curious what your thoughts are on guilty pleasures! Let me know in the comments below. ⬇️

We’ll continue the conversation and do Part 2 of our "Food & Pleasure" theme this Saturday, September 4th at 15:00 UTC 🤤

En este video, ... mi respuesta a la pregunta: "¿Cuál es tu 'placer pecaminoso'?" en un Live Q&A con mis @charlesxmichelpatrons por junio de 2019.

"Sola dosis facit venenum" /// "La dosis hace el veneno" 🌿💊 una versión condensada de la máxima del químico y filósofo Paracelso, "Todas las cosas son veneno, y nada es libre de veneno; la dosis sola hace que una cosa sea o no veneno."

Me da curiosidad saber qué opinan de los (mal llamados) "pecados" de placer (o 'placeres culpables' como se les dice en inglés). Comenten aquí abajo! ⬇️

Continuaremos la conversación y haremos la segunda parte de nuestro tema "Comida y placer" este sábado 4 de septiembre a las 15:00 UTC 🤤

This is an excerpt from my #TEDxBucharest talk called 🗣 Delicious Evolution - Food and Human Civilization 🗣 that I gave in November 2019, and it resonates even deeper today. 

As we absorb the realties of the #ipcc #climatereport AND explore the theme of Food & Pleasure over the next several weeks, I pose this question to you. 

❓How do YOU think we can use food as a medium to bring back balance in our relationship to each other, and nature? 🌽⚖️👥

I invite you to share your perspective in the comments, and if you want see more of this #TEDTalk, click the link in my bio!
